FBIS3-10084 "drlat040_o_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Mar 1994 Colombia City Mayor Celebrates Withdrawal of U.S. Troops PA0103131594 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 1 Mar 94 PA0103131594 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From "Caracol's 0600 to 0900" newscast] [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota -- (Gustavo Alvarez Larrazabal), the controversial mayor of the city of Tulua, has celebrated the withdrawal of U.S. troops from the Juanchaco area and issued a special decree calling for the full hoisting of the flag, which was at half-mast up to today. He has announced simultaneously he will preside over a ceremony at the main plaza to hoist the flag to the top of the mast at the City Mayor's Office. The flag had been hoisted at half-mast when the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers arrived. In the municipal decree, the city mayor said he trusts foreign soldiers will never again arrive there without complying with legal requirements.
